        {
            "review_id": "226338101",
            "steam_id": "76561198089577965",
            "playtime_minutes": 3048,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.5185185670852661,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "definitely one of the better Mario Party inspired games out there. Grab a couple friends and have some fun every now and then.\r\nAlso added workshop support some time ago, so if you don't like the base broth, then make your own soup."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226986838",
            "steam_id": "76561198322263187",
            "playtime_minutes": 1185,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Pummel Party is such a goated game, it's just that the connectivity issues tend to make the experience a bit worse. They added some patches to make it so that it's a bit easier to rejoin a game if you disconnect, but the player who disconnected can't join in until after the mini-game, which is a bit disheartening for some players. Other than that, love this game!"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226739388",
            "steam_id": "76561198276733237",
            "playtime_minutes": 559,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Great PC/Steam alternative to the Mario Party experience- with the added benefit of a massive Steam Workshop of boards and minigames. \r\n\r\nNo public lobbies left, but if you have some friends to play this with- great option for this genre. There's a couple poorly designed base game minigames, not a tremendous board selection- especially smaller maps for 3 players- and the visual style is serviceable, but not much more. Doesn't really add anything unique to the genre. But those are all relatively minor issues for what this game is. If you keep all that in mind, and that works for you and your group- plenty of potential hours of fun. 7/10"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226582215",
            "steam_id": "76561198018636884",
            "playtime_minutes": 1393,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Most fun party game on PC in my humble opinion, you can freely customize your ruleset and there's plenty of great maps and minigames on the Workshop."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226344698",
            "steam_id": "76561198815021196",
            "playtime_minutes": 458,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "The game is a lot of fun, especially with friends, with lots of minigames that don't really make sense, but my only problem with it is the price of 15 euros. Unfortunately, the game doesn't show who knows what and for 15 euros it's not worth it, better wait until there's a discount on Steam for it. Anyway, the game is 9/10, it would have been 10/10, but it's not a 15 euro game it s more of a 5 euro game."
        },
